# Google preview after every task

After completing any task that touches the website (UI, routes, components, CSS, copy, signup flows):

1. **Ensure dev server** — `npm run dev:arena` on port **3004** (kill busy port first if needed).
2. **Open Google Chrome** to the relevant preview URL (default: http://localhost:3004/#home).
3. **Tell the user** the URL and remind **Cmd+Shift+R** hard refresh.

## Default URLs

| Area | URL |
|------|-----|
| Home · Front 12 slots | http://localhost:3004/#home |
| Intl SUITE | http://localhost:3004/rooms/international-suite |
| Japan room | http://localhost:3004/rooms/japan-room |
| Signup / JOIN (slot click) | http://localhost:3004/#home → click available slot |

## Commands

```bash
# Dev (repo or Desktop copy)
npm run dev:arena

# Open Chrome (macOS)
open -a "Google Chrome" "http://localhost:3004/#home"
```

Do this **at the end of the response** — do not skip unless the task was docs-only or unrelated to the site.
